        5.0 out of 5 stars Surprised by its performance for the price.
        Reviewed in the United States on May 15, 2020
        Before I start just wanted to mention that no one encouraged me to leave this review. I Received these may 14 and to be honest my first impression on them Was that I felt like I wasted my money but I realized I didnt put them in correctly. They are really big and look kinda awkward. Once I looked at the pic on the box of how it should look in my ear and changing the ear tip I quickly realized these headphones are pretty damn good. Great sharp bass and sound the only drawback is the mids are taken for a backseat on this one. Battery is excellent, Its made for workouts and it stays in your ear. As far as a great fit goes this one takes the cake with other buds Ive used. I also own the AirPod pros and Jabra Active elite 75t so I have a decent sense of what sounds good. These are definitely a must buy for what you get if you didnt wanna invest in a little more for those noise canceling premium buds. The longer I listened to These with different genres of music I Can really appreciate them for what they are.

        2.0 out of 5 stars Good but expensive for what you get...
        Reviewed in the United States on May 4, 2020
        Color: BlueVerified Purchase
        Overall I would say they are pretty good but they are a bit overpriced for the features that you get. These should be $60. They are nothing special. You can get some Galaxy Buds+ for the same price or less and get a lot more features.

        Pros:
        - Simple button controls (button could have been a bit lower to make it easier to press)
        - Great sound w/ a huge emphasis on bass (a bit too much IMO).
        - Light and comfortable.
        - Good seal in the ear.
        - Block out noise pretty well.
        - USB-C charging port.
        - Microphone sounds really good but does pick up background noise pretty well.
        - No Active Noise Cancelling - ANC is a joke and waste of money on anything that doesn't cover all or most your ears.

        Cons:
        - No multipoint (no pairing/switching between multiple devices).
        - Cannot use the right earbud on its own (only the left one or both).
        - Matte finish isn't the greatest feeling (makes them feel a bit cheap).
        - Earbuds are on the larger side and stick out a bit.

        Reviewed in India on June 28, 2020
        Color: BlueVerified Purchase
        Writing this after using it for a week. I own a Bose Soundsport TWS, so, my comparison is with Bose.
        Battery - Excellent, no complaints. 9-10 hours. 5 STAR.
        Calls - during phone calls, other side caller can hear you clearly but you will hear a hollow effect, like the caller is talking through a PVC tube. So, I give 4 STAR
        BT Connectvity - I did not face any problems with Left & Right connectivity on calls or music. For Calls, you can use Left earbud independently or both together.
        Good with my iphone 11 but drops intermittently when connected to PC for music or calls, breaks 6-7 times average per minute but reconnects immediately within a sec. - 4 STAR (for calls)
        Music - Excellent. Bass/LF is excellent, Mid frequency is also good. in the HF department, it is slightly less, maybe 5% to 7%. Stereo separation is better than Bose. Overall, SONY WF-XB 700 is excellent.
        Fitting is excellent, Wearing it for 4-5 hours does not pain or hurt and I even forgot that I have a earbud in my ear. (with Bose, I remove it every time after calls).
        The only CON is, the plastic lid is very flimsy and cheap and always seed a fear of breaking any moment.

        5.0 out of 5 stars Excelentes Graves
        Reviewed in Mexico on September 2, 2020
        Color: BlueVerified Purchase
        Estuve viendo varios reviews sobre estos audfonos y me decid a comprarlos por la calidad de sonido que se mensiona en todos.

        Recin recib los audfonos ayer, 20 minutos justo antes de ir al gimnasio, y a partir de esto, todo han sido gratas sorpresas. En estos 20 minutos los empareje al celular y los cargu en el estuche en lo que me trasladaba a entrenar. Me dur la batera una hora y media por la carga rpida. La comodidad y el aislamiento de ruido ( Sello ) son excelentes. La conexin es estable sin problemas. Y el sonido es espectacular, especialmente si eres como yo, un "Bass Head". Lo graves son profundos y claros sin distorsin. Los agudos son super claros sin molestar y los medios se sienten con buen nivel. Me encant la firma de sonido de estos audfonos. El volumen es alto, por lo que no tendrs problemas en este aspecto. La imagen 3D del sonido, a diferencia de la mayora de audfonos en este segmento, se siente con una gran separacin en el espacio de los instrumentos. Es como si estuvieras en un lugar muy grande.

        En los reviews que vi antes, se dice que el tamao de los audfonos es muy grande, y pues, para gustos colores. A m me gust el diseo. Si eres de odos pequeos, probablemente no sean tan cmodos para ti. Note que no se mueven durante el entrenamiento.

        El micrfono para las llamadas es bueno.

        Tengo unos Amps Air 2.0 y unos Sabath e12, tambin tienen buen sonido, pero los Amps no son tan cmodos y les dura solo Hora y media la batera. Los Sabath me los tengo que estar acomodando constantemente porque se pierde el sello. En resumen estos audfonos Sony son super comodos, tienen carga rpida, 9 horas de batera, y un excelente sonido. Si te gustan los audfonos con graves profundos son para ti. Cmo contra yo pondra que para las personas con odos pequeos podrian no sean tan cmodos, y que no cuentan con sensores de proximidad para que se inicie la msica de forma automtica. En general los recomiendo.
